set="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91b7c971-f769-4005-bff9-afd833e6a646_678x651.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91b7c971-f769-4005-bff9-afd833e6a646_678x651.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91b7c971-f769-4005-bff9-afd833e6a646_678x651.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91b7c971-f769-4005-bff9-afd833e6a646_678x651.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91b7c971-f769-4005-bff9-afd833e6a646_678x651.jpeg" width="678" height="651" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/91b7c971-f769-4005-bff9-afd833e6a646_678x651.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:651,&quot;width&quot;:678,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:194053,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91b7c971-f769-4005-bff9-afd833e6a646_678x651.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91b7c971-f769-4005-bff9-afd833e6a646_678x651.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91b7c971-f769-4005-bff9-afd833e6a646_678x651.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F91b7c971-f769-4005-bff9-afd833e6a646_678x651.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>事实上，丰富的住房是新加坡如此富裕的主要原因之一。</p><p>当然，新加坡拥有如此多住房的原因是该国传说中的“公共”住房政策。那里<a href="https://www.policynote.ca/singapore-housing/">不乏</a><a href="https://www.thearcadiaonline.com/what-is-hdb-housing-and-how-does-it-work/">解释者</a>，但这里是基础知识。新加坡政府拥有大部分土地，并设有一个名为住房发展局（HDB）的政府机构，负责建造大量住房。然后，它以便宜的价格出售这些住房，主要卖给首次购房者（即年轻人）。然后谁可以自由转售它。首次购房者的折扣和政府让价格随着时间的推移缓慢而稳定升值的能力相结合，意味着组屋公寓不仅可以作为廉价的居住场所，而且可以作为一种积累财富的养老金制度。换句话说，在新加坡，用你的家作为居住的地方和用它来创造财富并不矛盾！</p><p>相当了不起。</p><p>好吧，我刚才说的一部分内容实际上并不正确。政府实际上并不向人们出售 HDB 公寓；而是向人们出售 HDB 公寓。它向他们出售 99 年的租约。如果租约还有98年，那就非常接近所有权了，所以当新加坡的制度开始时，它基本上是一个房屋所有权制度（事实上，新加坡的房屋被称为“永久业权”，或私人拥有，从技术上讲是999 年租约！）。请记住，新加坡成立于 1965 年，因此 99 年租约尚未到期。但再过几十年，这将成为一个令人头疼的问题，因为租约到期的人将不得不搬到新公寓。人们现在开始思考那一天，这会<a href="https://theindependent.sg/hdbs-99-year-time-bombs-are-ticking-dont-mess-around-with-them/">扰乱租赁市场</a>并导致一些公寓开始贬值。</p><p>对新加坡政府而言，99年租约是一项毫无意义的政策。只要政府拥有土地，如果需要重建旧建筑，它总是可以让居民搬走——基本上，这就像政府控制公寓协会的公寓一样。为每间公寓增加时间限制，这会让人们在任意日期搬出，这是一个不必要的额外步骤。</p><p>但抛开这个小问题不谈，新加坡的建屋发展局系统对于解决困扰大多数其他国家的住房问题来说绝对是一个令人惊奇的解决方案。基本上，政府拥有和开发土地可以控制住房供应，从而生产充足的经济适用房和可预测的缓慢升值。爱尔兰因<a href="https://www.irishtimes.com/ireland/housing-planning/2023/03/23/irelands-housing-crisis-facts-and-figures-all-you-need-to-know/">住房短缺而臭名昭著</a>，其制药业面临着将制药业输给新加坡的风险——新加坡是美国制药 FDI 的主要竞争对手，原因很简单，新加坡可以建造住房，而爱尔兰则不能。如果我负责爱尔兰，我会拼命寻找某种方式来效仿建屋发展局。</p><p>事实上，如果我也是美国人，我也会寻找效仿 HDB 的方法。事实上，拜登政府一直在<a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/biden-unveils-plan-increase-us-122815341.html">试图通过一项在我看来非常适合新加坡的试点计划</a>：</p><blockquote><p>拜登-哈里斯政府最近宣布了邻里房屋税收抵免，以及为特定首次购房者提供首付援助。该计划旨在为父母也从未拥有过住房的第一代或低财富买家创造一条拥有住房的途径。</p><p>邻里住宅税收抵免尚未获得国会签署。根据白宫 10 月 16 日星期一发表的声明，如果该法案获得通过，将拨款 160 亿美元资金在美国各地建造或修复 40 万套新住宅。此外，该计划还将提供 100 亿美元的首付援助和 1 亿美元用于补贴首次购房者。</p></blockquote><p>美国各州也应该研究类似的计划。</p><p>不管怎样，值得一提的是，并不是每个新加坡人——也不是每个中产阶级——都住在组屋里。尽管这个国家很小，但更远的地方也有一些郊区风格的地区，那里的大部分住房都是低层私人所有。很多看起来像这样： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4b3995b-2d23-4199-a293-bd5628ca7fd0_1542x2048.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4b3995b-2d23-4199-a293-bd5628ca7fd0_1542x2048.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4b3995b-2d23-4199-a293-bd5628ca7fd0_1542x2048.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4b3995b-2d23-4199-a293-bd5628ca7fd0_1542x2048.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4b3995b-2d23-4199-a293-bd5628ca7fd0_1542x2048.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4b3995b-2d23-4199-a293-bd5628ca7fd0_1542x2048.jpeg" width="1456" height="1934" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/a4b3995b-2d23-4199-a293-bd5628ca7fd0_1542x2048.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1934,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:796690,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4b3995b-2d23-4199-a293-bd5628ca7fd0_1542x2048.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4b3995b-2d23-4199-a293-bd5628ca7fd0_1542x2048.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4b3995b-2d23-4199-a293-bd5628ca7fd0_1542x2048.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4b3995b-2d23-4199-a293-bd5628ca7fd0_1542x2048.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>这不是一座带草坪的宽敞牧场房屋，但它有<em>很大</em>的居住空间，并且有足够的隐私。然而，这种建筑使得一个区域非常密集，即使没有高层建筑。在美国，这当然是一个“缺失的中间”选择。</p><h4>新加坡步行街</h4><p>现在，我要说的是新加坡的城市环境让我困扰的一件事。令人惊讶的是，它的布局以汽车为中心。</p><p>新加坡人大多乘坐火车和公共汽车出行； <a href="https://www.deccanherald.com/world/singapores-car-lite-policy-reduces-car-ownership-to-one-third-down-from-40-in-2013-2758732">只有三分之一</a>的人口拥有汽车。火车系统很棒——虽然不如日本的好，但也没有什么好。步行游览非常方便。</p><p>但是当您四处走动时，您经常会走在一条非常大的街道一侧的狭窄人行道上。例如，这是我在小印度拍摄的照片，这是新加坡最具活力的民族社区之一： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e51b7b2-f1d5-4e2a-9680-91f734cd06b8_616x819.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e51b7b2-f1d5-4e2a-9680-91f734cd06b8_616x819.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e51b7b2-f1d5-4e2a-9680-91f734cd06b8_616x819.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e51b7b2-f1d5-4e2a-9680-91f734cd06b8_616x819.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e51b7b2-f1d5-4e2a-9680-91f734cd06b8_616x819.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e51b7b2-f1d5-4e2a-9680-91f734cd06b8_616x819.jpeg" width="616" height="819" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/6e51b7b2-f1d5-4e2a-9680-91f734cd06b8_616x819.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:819,&quot;width&quot;:616,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:227078,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e51b7b2-f1d5-4e2a-9680-91f734cd06b8_616x819.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e51b7b2-f1d5-4e2a-9680-91f734cd06b8_616x819.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e51b7b2-f1d5-4e2a-9680-91f734cd06b8_616x819.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6e51b7b2-f1d5-4e2a-9680-91f734cd06b8_616x819.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>主要购物街是一条巨大的四车道道路！当我拍摄这张照片时，交通并不多（部分原因是我一直等到没有汽车阻挡拍摄），但汽车经过的频率足够高，以至于你会吸入大量废气。</p><p>这种情况并不是特别罕见。市中心的大部分地区都布满了比上图大得多<a href="https://twitter.com/Noahpinion/status/1722158747043381359">的巨大主干道</a>，而且城市的许多商店和餐馆都位于这些道路的两侧。结果是，人们常常感觉新加坡是一座为汽车而建的城市，尽管汽车保有量相当低。</p><p>事实上，美国人对这样的大道有一个词：“stroads”。 “stroad”<a href="https://www.strongtowns.org/journal/2018/3/1/whats-a-stroad-and-why-does-it-matter">由城市主义非营利组织 Strong Towns 创造</a>，指的是一条宽阔的高速路，行人也可以沿着这条路散步和购物。美国的情况比新加坡差，但新加坡也有不少。</p><p>关于新加坡为何选择这种发展模式的理论有很多——有人说这是卡车运输和物流所必需的，也有人说政府优先考虑富裕车主的利益。与我交谈过的人甚至表示，在新加坡动荡的早期历史中，宽阔的街道被认为有助于控制骚乱。无论如何，在一个以行人为中心的城市里，有如此多的土地面积供汽车使用，这很奇怪。</p><p>解决这个问题的方法是拓宽人行道。人行道狭窄的道路对行人来说感觉不安全，因为你离汽车太近了。它还使行人与汽车尾气密切接触。这对于散步来说并不是特别好： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e727a78-5936-4e97-b97e-82711812e843_512x680.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e727a78-5936-4e97-b97e-82711812e843_512x680.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e727a78-5936-4e97-b97e-82711812e843_512x680.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e727a78-5936-4e97-b97e-82711812e843_512x680.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e727a78-5936-4e97-b97e-82711812e843_512x680.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e727a78-5936-4e97-b97e-82711812e843_512x680.jpeg" width="512" height="680" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7e727a78-5936-4e97-b97e-82711812e843_512x680.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:680,&quot;width&quot;:512,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:113647,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e727a78-5936-4e97-b97e-82711812e843_512x680.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e727a78-5936-4e97-b97e-82711812e843_512x680.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e727a78-5936-4e97-b97e-82711812e843_512x680.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e727a78-5936-4e97-b97e-82711812e843_512x680.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>拓宽这些人行道将使人们远离汽车，并允许安装栏杆和其他障碍物，让人们有一种受到保护的感觉，免受汽车的冲撞。这可能需要牺牲一些交通车道，但是哦，好吧。</p><p>这是新加坡更适合行人的街道的一个很好的例子： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e48c842-2c2e-405a-8c2c-c7e81d4dbac2_678x676.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e48c842-2c2e-405a-8c2c-c7e81d4dbac2_678x676.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e48c842-2c2e-405a-8c2c-c7e81d4dbac2_678x676.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e48c842-2c2e-405a-8c2c-c7e81d4dbac2_678x676.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e48c842-2c2e-405a-8c2c-c7e81d4dbac2_678x676.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e48c842-2c2e-405a-8c2c-c7e81d4dbac2_678x676.jpeg" width="678" height="676" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7e48c842-2c2e-405a-8c2c-c7e81d4dbac2_678x676.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:676,&quot;width&quot;:678,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:245446,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e48c842-2c2e-405a-8c2c-c7e81d4dbac2_678x676.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e48c842-2c2e-405a-8c2c-c7e81d4dbac2_678x676.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e48c842-2c2e-405a-8c2c-c7e81d4dbac2_678x676.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7e48c842-2c2e-405a-8c2c-c7e81d4dbac2_678x676.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>如果我是新加坡政府，我的目标是修建更多这样的街道。如果他们有能力以零虫子的方式将城市覆盖在修剪整齐的绿色植物中，他们就有能力打造对行人来说更加舒适的街道。</p><p>不管怎样，抛开远足，如果你还没有的话，你绝对应该去新加坡看看。惊人的财富和未来主义的太阳朋克建筑只是其中的两个景点——还有美味的食物、有趣的民族社区、美丽的景色、有趣的历史和相当壮观的多样化建筑风格。</p><p>记住不要不小心带任何大麻，否则他们会<a href="https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/up-to-30-years-jail-for-possession-of-cannabis-with-roll-out-of-stricter-drug-laws-from-june">用拐杖打你，然后把你送进监狱几十年</a>。 </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/singapore-urbanism?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/singapore-urbanism?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p>; 
Yes, it's possible to imagine progressive dystopias We shouldn't just worry about the means of progress, but the ends as well. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/yes-its-possible-to-imagine-progressive https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/yes-its-possible-to-imagine-progressiveNoah Smith Fri, 10 Nov 2023 07:52:40 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg" width="722" height="481.3333333333333" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:624,&quot;width&quot;:936,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:722,&quot;bytes&quot;:135733,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption"> “<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/53301297@N00/14486751845">唯一可持续的增长是去增长</a>”， <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/53301297@N00">pasa47</a> ， <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/?ref=openverse">CC BY 2.0</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>最近有一个想法一直困扰着我。几个月前，布拉德·德隆和我<a href="https://braddelong.substack.com/p/podcast-hexapodia-liii-rule-1-no#details">做了一个播客</a>，我们讨论了布丽安娜·吴、马特·伊格莱西亚斯和埃兹拉·克莱因等中左派人士对一些左派人士的反击。布拉德将这些阻力归结为从根本上讲是<em>策略</em>问题——在他看来，布里安娜、马特和埃兹拉对一些进步人士在试图实现乌托邦时使用的手段感到沮丧，并主张采取更务实、更有效的方法。这是一个长期传统的一部分，倡导社会变革的积极分子争论社会已经准备好进行多大程度的变革。</p><p>虽然我确实认为确实存在一些问题，但我不同意布拉德的观点，即这主要是阻力的原因。相反，我认为，我们真正看到的是，人们对进步主义者似乎正在争取的一些<em>目标</em>越来越感到不安——与其说是关于变革的步伐，不如说是关于变革的方向。当布拉德要求我列出一些反乌托邦进步愿景的例子时，我立即说“去生长”，他同意了。</p><p>不管怎样，请注意我说的是“一些”这个词。许多进步的愿景，比如更大的经济平等、缩小种族贫富差距以及扭转气候变化，都是我想要的！如果你将这篇文章解读为说进步主义<em>大体上</em>是一个反乌托邦项目，那么你就严重误解了我。我也不是说保守主义比进步主义更好，或者说政治右翼不包含自己的反乌托邦愿景。确实如此。</p><p>相反，我想说的是，进步派在 2010 年代的狂热浪潮中所接受的一些重大思想是误导性的，应该被抛弃，以便努力实现人类真正想要生活的乌托邦。</p><p>这里列出了四个这样的愿景。</p><h4>退生长</h4><p>当然，这是对布拉德问题的简单回答。我已经写了多篇文章，详细论证了为什么停止或逆转经济增长（这一想法在过去十年中在一些进步人士中变得流行）作为限制人类环境影响的一种方式既不可行，也不受欢迎。首先，我认为去增长所需的生活水平下降使其在政治上成为不可能的事情，并且所涉及的全球中央计划的数量将无法实施： </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;52bf6b2d-b886-46cf-8a98-7325f073a207&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;I was going to write a lengthy post explaining why &#8220;degrowth&#8221; &#8212; the idea that we need to halt economic growth in order to save the planet &#8212; is a very bad idea. But in the meantime, other people have written that post, or recorded that podcast, and done it well. These include&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;People are realizing that degrowth is bad&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2021-09-06T08:40:54.095Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Faeddab2a-6c56-4e5b-9c35-9ca0fecd86bd_1024x682.jpeg&quot;,&quot;cover_image_alt&quot;:null,&quot;canonical_url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/people-are-realizing-that-degrowth&quot;,&quot;section_name&quot;:null,&quot;id&quot;:39760555,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;reaction_count&quot;:129,&quot;comment_count&quot;:106,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Noahpinion&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04281755-2cd6-42e5-a496-e69153abebb2_281x281.png&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false}"></div><p>我还认为，解决气候变化需要增长，因为用太阳能、风能和电池取代我们的能源需要<em>大量</em>的经济产出。一旦我们转向这些能源，它们就会变得非常便宜（由于学习曲线），我们实际上会比以前持续更高的消耗。</p><p>在后续文章中，我批评了去增长想法背后的研究和言论，这些想法通常基于意识形态驱动的伪科学： </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;15f58e2c-0355-411d-a35f-7e2969e03f23&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A year and a half ago, I wrote a post entitled &#8220;People are realizing that degrowth is bad&#8221;. Around that time, the degrowth movement had started to receive a bit of attention in the U.S., as part of the general push for major action on climate change. But writers like&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Degrowth: We can't let it happen here!&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2023-05-24T01:54:00.942Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F058020be-b262-4c24-88c2-ba3e1c8e0184_1024x681.jpeg&quot;,&quot;cover_image_alt&quot;:null,&quot;canonical_url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/degrowth-we-cant-let-it-happen-here&quot;,&quot;section_name&quot;:null,&quot;id&quot;:123140587,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;reaction_count&quot;:201,&quot;comment_count&quot;:80,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Noahpinion&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04281755-2cd6-42e5-a496-e69153abebb2_281x281.png&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true}"></div><p>正如我在第二篇文章中所解释的，我认为去增长在一定程度上是一种平衡国家衰落的尝试，这就是为什么这个想法在欧洲比在美国更受欢迎的原因</p><p>我不想彻底解决这一点，但我认为有必要强调去增长的未来将是多么令人不快和不人道。富裕国家的人民将被迫接受低得多的生活水平，而发展中国家的人民将面临<a href="https://brankomilanovic.substack.com/p/degrowth-solving-the-impasse-by-magical">更加渺茫的未来</a>。这种情况无疑会引起不满，导致对强制实现大规模贫困的领导人的强烈抵制。在推翻去增长政权之后，我们会看到钟摆完全转向承诺无限资源消耗的领导人，此时环境将比以前更糟。除此之外，经济衰退将使投资绿色能源和其他保护环境的技术变得更加困难。</p><p>因此，虽然我认为我们确实需要担心增长的潜在负面后果，并尽最大努力减轻这些危害，但我认为，为了拯救环境而试图让自己陷入贫困，对我们和环境来说都将是一个灾难性的错误。这不是任何进步人士应该为之奋斗的事情。</p><h4>驱逐“殖民者”</h4><p>非殖民化，正如我们通常使用的词——即国家从欧洲帝国霸主手中获得独立——在我出生时实际上已经完成。这对世界来说是一件非常好的事情，无论是在道德上还是<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/against-hickelism">在经济上</a>。但近年来，美国的一些进步人士开始谈论一种完全不同类型的“非殖民化”——将“殖民者”人口驱逐出其祖先定居的地区。</p><p> “非殖民化”的这种另类含义在人文学术界、一些左倾媒体和激进运动中流行了一段时间，但在哈马斯 10 月 7 日袭击以色列后，它突然登上了国家舞台。在哈马斯的屠杀和强奸狂欢发生后，《Teen Vogue》杂志的作家 Najma Sharif 发布了以下推文： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2