e><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>换句话说，凯尔特之虎看起来很像亚洲四小龙——一个生产大量高科技产品并将其销往世界其他地区的国家。当然，一个国家无法仅靠出口制造业生存——需要有强劲的当地经济来流通和<a href="https://eml.berkeley.edu/~moretti/multipliers.pdf">倍增</a>出口收入的收益。但出于多种原因，出口制造业是有用的。制造业本质上往往具有快速的生产率增长。许多人认为，出口还可以通过迫使本地公司在全球市场上竞争并帮助他们吸收外国技术来<a href="https://www.imf.org/en/Publications/WP/Issues/2019/03/26/The-Return-of-the-Policy-That-Shall-Not-Be-Named-Principles-of-Industrial-Policy-46710">提高生产率</a>。</p><p>爱尔兰能够实现这一目标的原因之一是其与美国和欧洲这两个重要经济体的特殊关系。</p><h4>来自美国的投资，欧洲市场</h4><p>如果您想大量出口，您需要有地方销售您的产品。爱尔兰的出口目的地实际上非常多元化： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F210454e3-9667-4025-82ba-642a5b602592_722x666.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F210454e3-9667-4025-82ba-642a5b602592_722x666.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F210454e3-9667-4025-82ba-642a5b602592_722x666.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F210454e3-9667-4025-82ba-642a5b602592_722x666.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F210454e3-9667-4025-82ba-642a5b602592_722x666.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F210454e3-9667-4025-82ba-642a5b602592_722x666.jpeg" width="636" height="586.6703601108034" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/210454e3-9667-4025-82ba-642a5b602592_722x666.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:666,&quot;width&quot;:722,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:636,&quot;bytes&quot;:130828,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F210454e3-9667-4025-82ba-642a5b602592_722x666.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F210454e3-9667-4025-82ba-642a5b602592_722x666.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F210454e3-9667-4025-82ba-642a5b602592_722x666.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F210454e3-9667-4025-82ba-642a5b602592_722x666.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">来源： <a href="https://oec.world/en/profile/country/irl?yearSelector1=2021">OEC</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>欧洲显然是这里最大的，这并不奇怪，因为地理位置很接近。但爱尔兰是欧盟的一部分——而且在此之前是欧洲经济共同体的一部分——这一事实肯定会有所帮助。爱尔兰对欧洲的拥抱与英国形成鲜明对比，英国的经济<a href="https://cepr.org/voxeu/columns/impact-brexit-uk-economy-reviewing-evidence">仍因脱欧而陷入困境</a>。</p><p>但在投资资本方面，爱尔兰还有一张更大的王牌——美国。正如<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-polandmalaysia-model">波兰和马来西亚等</a>其他新兴发展明星一样，外国直接投资对爱尔兰经济非常重要。美国是迄今为止最大的投资来源国。这是新西兰外交和贸易部<a href="https://www.mfat.govt.nz/en/trade/mfat-market-reports/foreign-direct-investment-in-ireland-june-2023/">最近的一份报告</a>：</p><blockquote><p>按人均计算，爱尔兰是欧盟新外国直接投资 (FDI) 项目最受欢迎的目的地。自 1960 年代以来，吸引 FDI 一直是爱尔兰政府政策的基石，而 FDI 现在在支持爱尔兰经济方面发挥着非常重要的作用……</p><p>投资主要来自美国，海外的大量爱尔兰侨民帮助促进了联系。 2020年，美国对爱尔兰的直接投资达到3900亿美元，超过美国对巴西、俄罗斯、印度、中国和南非（金砖五国）的总和。尽管所有行业的投资都受到欢迎，但那些提供高价值出口产品（例如信息通信技术和制药）的行业受到青睐……</p><p>从全球分布来看，在爱尔兰投资的跨国公司中有 847 家来自美国，354 家来自欧洲，其中近一半来自德国和法国，136 家来自英国，212 家来自其他地区世界的[。]</p></blockquote><p><a href="https://www.civitas.org.uk/content/files/industrialpolicyintherepublicofireland.pdf">我读到的一份报告</a>将爱尔兰称为“硅谷和欧洲之间的中间人”。</p><p>正如报告所提到的，美国拥有大量爱尔兰侨民——约<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Irish_Americans">3600 万</a>，是爱尔兰人口的七倍多。但在美国和爱尔兰之间建立联系的不仅仅是侨民——而是侨民的<em>想法</em>。由于爱尔兰人是美国建国后第一批来到美国的外国工人，他们的故事对于美国作为一个移民国家的自我认同至关重要。许多没有爱尔兰血统的美国人喜欢想象自己有爱尔兰血统—— <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Americans_of_Irish_descent#:~:text=At%20least%2022%20presidents%20of,has%20strong%20documented%20Irish%20origins.">例如比尔·克林顿(Bill Clinton)</a> ，他声称的爱尔兰血统永远无法得到证实。每个人在圣帕特里克节都会喝醉。</p><p>这种对祖先的依恋和情感的结合显示了强大的侨民的力量。几个世纪以来，爱尔兰将<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Irish_diaspora">年轻人送往国外</a>的倾向历来被视为一种弱点。自 1990 年以来，爱尔兰一直是一个实例，说明移民如何回旋并最终成为一种力量。</p><h4>爱尔兰的政策决定了一切</h4><p>粗略地说，发展政策有三种。这些都是：</p><ul><li><p>自由化</p></li><li><p>能力建设</p></li><li><p>产业政策</p></li></ul><p>自由化只是意味着消除经济活动的障碍——高税收、监管、贸易壁垒等等。能力建设意味着投资于教育、卫生和基础设施等领域。产业政策可能有很多不同的含义，从补贴出口到吸引外国投资，再到促进特定产业发展。</p><p>对这些方法争论不休的人们写了很多文章，但当你查看开发成功案例时，你会发现它们往往都涉及其中的某些部分。爱尔兰也不例外。</p><p>爱尔兰的自由化之旅很早就开始了。即使早在 20 世纪 50 年代，当爱尔兰主要出口农产品时，其领导人<a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/42912423">就认识到外国市场准入的重要性</a>。 20 世纪 70 年代，像<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/T._K._Whitaker">TK Whitaker</a>这样的经济政策影响者成功地主张自由贸易——如果你是一个没有太多国内市场的小国，自由贸易就至关重要。当然，欧洲经济共同体和欧盟对此至关重要。事实上，小国相对于大国的一大增长优势可能就是贸易开放性。在一个小国家，每个人都意识到国内市场是不够的。</p><p>爱尔兰的企业税率也是出了名的低，这也是爱尔兰享有避税天堂美誉的部分原因（另一部分原因是一些奇怪的税收漏洞）。但事实上，情况并非总是如此。直到 90 年代末，爱尔兰对各种企业收入都实行<em>高</em>税率，但制造业除外，制造业的税率非常低： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F26187d30-ffa9-4349-8202-3100904216c2_600x580.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F26187d30-ffa9-4349-8202-3100904216c2_600x580.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F26187d30-ffa9-4349-8202-3100904216c2_600x580.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F26187d30-ffa9-4349-8202-3100904216c2_600x580.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F26187d30-ffa9-4349-8202-3100904216c2_600x580.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F26187d30-ffa9-4349-8202-3100904216c2_600x580.jpeg" width="600" height="580" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/26187d30-ffa9-4349-8202-3100904216c2_600x580.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:580,&quot;width&quot;:600,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:60359,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F26187d30-ffa9-4349-8202-3100904216c2_600x580.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F26187d30-ffa9-4349-8202-3100904216c2_600x580.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F26187d30-ffa9-4349-8202-3100904216c2_600x580.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F26187d30-ffa9-4349-8202-3100904216c2_600x580.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">作者：Britishfinance -<a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?curid=74620395">自己的作品</a>，CC BY-SA 4.0</figcaption></figure></div><p>这是自由化和产业政策的结合。制造业的优惠低利率帮助经济活动偏向于电子和制药等领域；如果没有这种分割利率，爱尔兰可能会像英国一样成为金融重镇。</p><p>事实上，人们想知道降低其他类型企业收入的税率是否可能无意中将爱尔兰的投资从凯尔特老虎时期的优势转向房地产投机和避税天堂等恶作剧。但避税天堂的<a href="https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/abs/10.1086/tpe.19.20061896">增长速度也往往快</a>于其他国家。部分原因可能是，许多税收制度只允许公司在实际将工厂迁往该国时才能利用该国的低税率。因此，爱尔兰可能会通过税收套利吸引企业来吸收外国技术。</p><p> Partly as a result of low tax rates and various other business-friendly policies, Ireland regularly ranks near the top of various “competitiveness” rankings; in 2023 it was <a href="https://www.imd.org/centers/wcc/world-competitiveness-center/rankings/world-competitiveness-ranking/2023/">#2 on IMD&#39;s global list</a> , behind only Denmark, with especially high rankings in “business efficiency” and “government efficiency”.</p><p> Some thinkers like Ha-Joon Chang have concerns with FDI as a driver of development. They worry that foreign companies won&#39;t let go of their best technologies, and that foreign brands will crowd out domestic ones, ultimately limiting a nation&#39;s ascension to the top of the value chain. Irish policymakers have shared this concern, <a href="https://www.civitas.org.uk/content/files/industrialpolicyintherepublicofireland.pdf">making various attempts</a> to promote domestic innovation. So far it&#39;s not clear how effective this has been (especially because Ireland&#39;s tax shenanigans make macro data difficult to assess).</p><p> And of course to build a rich economy, one thing you definitely need is a lot of skilled labor. There are two ways to get skilled labor — education and immigration — and in general you should use both. Ireland did. Its baby boom was bigger and lasted much longer than other rich countries: </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5310ac3c-b7a5-4791-81a1-428171e54811_1020x720.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5310ac3c-b7a5-4791-81a1-428171e54811_1020x720.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5310ac3c-b7a5-4791-81a1-428171e54811_1020x720.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5310ac3c-b7a5-4791-81a1-428171e54811_1020x720.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5310ac3c-b7a5-4791-81a1-428171e54811_1020x720.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5310ac3c-b7a5-4791-81a1-428171e54811_1020x720.jpeg" width="1020" height="720" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5310ac3c-b7a5-4791-81a1-428171e54811_1020x720.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:720,&quot;width&quot;:1020,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:169711,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5310ac3c-b7a5-4791-81a1-428171e54811_1020x720.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5310ac3c-b7a5-4791-81a1-428171e54811_1020x720.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5310ac3c-b7a5-4791-81a1-428171e54811_1020x720.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5310ac3c-b7a5-4791-81a1-428171e54811_1020x720.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p> Ireland has also done a great job of educating its young people, with <a href="https://data.oecd.org/eduatt/population-with-tertiary-education.htm">one of the highest rates</a> of tertiary education in the OECD.</p><p> But Ireland has also imported large numbers of workers. In the 90s, a traditional pattern of outmigration reversed, and people started moving to Ireland en masse: </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F215e8c2c-776d-4ca5-96fa-67e7928990b0_900x578.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F215e8c2c-776d-4ca5-96fa-67e7928990b0_900x578.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F215e8c2c-776d-4ca5-96fa-67e7928990b0_900x578.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F215e8c2c-776d-4ca5-96fa-67e7928990b0_900x578.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F215e8c2c-776d-4ca5-96fa-67e7928990b0_900x578.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F215e8c2c-776d-4ca5-96fa-67e7928990b0_900x578.jpeg" width="900" height="578" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/215e8c2c-776d-4ca5-96fa-67e7928990b0_900x578.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:578,&quot;width&quot;:900,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:113626,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F215e8c2c-776d-4ca5-96fa-67e7928990b0_900x578.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F215e8c2c-776d-4ca5-96fa-67e7928990b0_900x578.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F215e8c2c-776d-4ca5-96fa-67e7928990b0_900x578.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F215e8c2c-776d-4ca5-96fa-67e7928990b0_900x578.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> Source: <a href="https://www.cso.ie/en/releasesandpublications/ep/p-pme/populationandmigrationestimatesapril2023/keyfindings/">CSO Ireland</a></figcaption></figure></div><p> These immigrants tend to skew young. And they&#39;re disproportionately high-skilled; in 2022, more than half of immigrants to Ireland <a href="https://mcginleylaw.ie/irish-immigration-statistics-2023/#:~:text=Over%2050%25%20of%20immigrants%20had,those%20seeking%20asylum%20in%20Ireland.">had a university degree or similar</a> . Some of this is <a href="https://personal.lse.ac.uk/minns/minns_jssisi_2005.pdf">natural self-selection</a> , but Ireland also has policies in place to promote skilled immigration.</p><p> They also come from a mix of countries. Ireland&#39;s Central Statistics Office <a href="https://www.cso.ie/en/releasesandpublications/ep/p-pme/populationandmigrationestimatesapril2023/keyfindings/">found that in 2022</a> there were 141,600 total immigrants, 29,600 of whom were returning Irish citizens. About 26,000 were from the EU, about 42,000 from Ukraine, 4800 from the UK, and about 39,000 from other countries.</p><p> At a time when many countries are becoming hostile to immigration or at least questioning its value, Ireland has generally continued to embrace foreign workers. There are some signs that East European immigrants <a href="https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/14782804.2022.2090321">aren&#39;t quite as successful</a> as their West European and global counterparts, and I did encounter a couple instances of stereotypes being leveled at East Europeans during my stay in Kilkenny. In the last year there has been a small <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/mar/21/ireland-anti-refugee-protests-far-right-uk-politics">backlash against refugees</a> .</p><p> But overall, Irish people are consistently <a href="https://odi.org/en/publications/public-narratives-and-attitudes-towards-refugees-and-other-migrants-ireland-country-profile/">more positive about immigration</a> than almost <a href="https://heartsandminds.odi.digital/country?country=ie">anyone else in Europe</a> . And for what it&#39;s worth, my brief personal experience bore this out. Irish people I talked to seemed very aware of how important foreign workers — especially skilled workers — had been to their country&#39;s economic ascent. Some mentioned pub culture and sports as key mechanisms of cultural integration. Others opined that Ireland was a “high EQ country”, whose people specialized in managing top engineers from all over the world. Nobody I talked to seemed to regard Irish immigration policy as anything other than a smashing success.</p><p> In other words, there are a lot of things Ireland did to try to produce an economic miracle. It liberalized its trade policy, cut taxes, created a favorable climate for business, and drew in a bunch of immigrants. But it also encouraged manufacturing, tried to promote domestic innovation, and invested heavily in education. Ireland did it all, and somehow, it worked out.</p><h4> What next for the Celtic Tiger?</h4><p> Ireland&#39;s biggest policy challenge right now, without a doubt, is housing. Rapid immigration, along with replacement-level fertility, has sparked a population boom: </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1525780b-17f3-467c-9059-d32c861a305b_913x576.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1525780b-17f3-467c-9059-d32c861a305b_913x576.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1525780b-17f3-467c-9059-d32c861a305b_913x576.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1525780b-17f3-467c-9059-d32c861a305b_913x576.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1525780b-17f3-467c-9059-d32c861a305b_913x576.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1525780b-17f3-467c-9059-d32c861a305b_913x576.jpeg" width="913" height="576" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/1525780b-17f3-467c-9059-d32c861a305b_913x576.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:576,&quot;width&quot;:913,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:65516,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1525780b-17f3-467c-9059-d32c861a305b_913x576.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1525780b-17f3-467c-9059-d32c861a305b_913x576.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1525780b-17f3-467c-9059-d32c861a305b_913x576.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1525780b-17f3-467c-9059-d32c861a305b_913x576.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> Source: <a href="https://www.cso.ie/en/releasesandpublications/ep/p-pme/populationandmigrationestimatesapril2023/keyfindings/">CSO Ireland</a></figcaption></figure></div><p> But this boom <a href="https://www.irishtimes.com/ireland/housing-planning/2023/03/23/irelands-housing-crisis-facts-and-figures-all-you-need-to-know/">hasn&#39;t been matched</a> by a boom in new housing construction. Ireland is still extremely wedded to the idea of single-family homes; very little of the population lives in apartments. The country&#39;&#39;s permitting process is possibly <a href="https://www.thefitzwilliam.com/p/a-simple-and-elegant-response-to">even more onerous</a> than America&#39;s; I met some YIMBYs who had come to Ireland to study the country&#39;s mistakes.</p><p> Housing is regularly listed as <a href="https://www.mfat.govt.nz/en/trade/mfat-market-reports/foreign-direct-investment-in-ireland-june-2023/">the biggest challenge</a> to continued FDI in Ireland, and overcrowding is probably one reason why anti-immigrant politics have finally made it to Ireland&#39;s shores. If the issue doesn&#39;t get solved, it&#39;s not inconceivable that Ireland could follow <a href="https://worksinprogress.co/issue/why-britain-doesnt-build">Britain into genteel decline</a> .</p><p> But for now, Ireland is still riding high on the success of its Celtic Tiger era. A country that was once subjugated and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anti-Irish_sentiment">looked down upon</a> by its neighbors is now a beacon of wealth and high-tech skill.</p><p> And I think this teaches us a crucial lesson about national development. If you went back to 1923 and asked people whether Ireland would be richer than the UK in a hundred years, how many of them do you think would have said yes? How many would have laughed in your face? And yet here we are, a century later, and that&#39;s the reality. Now pull out a map of the world, and pick out some countries that most people think don&#39;t have what it takes to get rich. Where do you think those countries will be in 100 years?</p><p> Are you sure? </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a> </p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-ireland-got-so-rich?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-ireland-got-so-rich?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><p> PS - Here are a few random (unedited) pics I took in Kilkenny…most are just standard “old castle and green countryside” stuff, but a couple show what the little downtown area looks like. </p><div class="image-gallery-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;gallery&quot;:{&quot;images&quot;:[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ec7821b6-13b3-4e10-a595-3d04f16b22f4_3072x4080.jpeg&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/aafa4108-346c-4cc7-bbb9-3b2058aff440_3072x4080.jpeg&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7053d0ab-b00c-4511-b36a-aa07cde0c9a7_3072x4080.jpeg&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/3316b253-58ef-41cb-a8fd-9e0f7a990a69_3072x4080.jpeg&quot;